21/06/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Four people were killed and one was injured early Monday (June 21st) in an armed clash in the town of Viti/Vitina, about 40km from the border with Macedonia. 
Three of those killed are citizens of Macedonia. 
Kosovo police said the shots came from a moving car, on the Viti/Vitina-Kllokot road. 
Macedonian Interior Minister Gordana Jankulovska confirmed the incident but did not elaborate, saying only that Macedonian authorities are in contact with Pristina and that more details can be expected later in the day. 
(Express, Telegrafi, Makfax - 21/06/10)
